{
  "stem": "5430.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And one of the things I recall that we had to-- I had to run to the Vistula-- Vistula River which runs across Warsaw to get water, just two buckets of water to bring home to drink.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And when I came back at one time I was running through like a tunnel of fire where both of the buildings on both sides of the streets were in flame-- in flames and collapsing all around me.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we were running right through in the middle of the street just to bring the two buckets of water to-- to have something to drink.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I know I'm running from one to another because I'm just flashing-- getting flashbacks.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't remember that other than the incident with the-- like I said, when they throwing out the bread for the propaganda purposes to show that they're feeding the crowds.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the incident with the Jew being cut off the beard on one side.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And-- but by that time-- oh, let me backtrack a little.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because when our house burned down, we took whatever we dug up from the basement and made bundles.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And each one had a preassigned bundle to-- to grab in case we had to run.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And my father, [NON-ENGLISH], arranged with my brother's fiancee's sister, who lived on [INAUDIBLE] Street, which is in the Jewish section in a big building.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And that building was protected by the military, because they-- I think they had the headquarters there.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Because they had the anti-aircraft guns on the roof.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And so that building was still standing.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they arranged with the military to send a soldier with a wagon to take our belongings to bring us over there from [INAUDIBLE] Street to [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I was elected to go with the wagon.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
